Initial Quality Assurance Mechanisms

Walkthrough Procedures: (Describe the walkthrough procedures followed in the project. Explain the steps involved, how they are conducted, and the key participants.)


Code Review Process: (Describe the code review process, including how it is carried out, the tools used, and the roles of team members involved.)


Software Evaluation Process: (Explain the processes used to assess software quality, such as user testing, performance benchmarking, and automated analysis tools.)


Quality Assurance Roles in the Team: (Outline the specific quality-related roles within the team, such as Quality Manager, Quality Engineer, Test Lead, and their responsibilities.)


Software Testing Methods: (Examine the source code to determine the presence of testing mechanisms such as unit tests, integration tests, and end-to-end tests. Describe their implementation or, if absent, recommend necessary testing methods.)


Identified Gaps and Recommendations: (Highlight any shortcomings in the quality assurance process and provide suggestions for improvement.)

